<SECOND>PM-Oscars-Other Awards,0391</SECOND>
<HEAD>Daniel Day-Lewis, Michelle Pfeiffer Dominate Pre-Oscar Film Awards</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Oscars, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of this season's top movie
awards handed out before tonight's Oscars:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   BEST PICTURE
   British Academy Awards: ``Dead Poets Society.''
   Golden Globes (drama): ``Born on the Fourth of July.''
   Golden Globes (comedy): ``Driving Miss Daisy.''
   National Board of Review: ``Driving Miss Daisy.''
   New York Film Critics Circle: ``My Left Foot.''
   National Society of Film Critics: ``Drugstore Cowboy.''
   Los Angeles Film Critics Association: ``Do the Right Thing.''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   BEST ACTOR
   British Academy Awards: Daniel Day-Lewis, ``My Left Foot.''
   Golden Globes (drama): Tom Cruise, ``Born on the Fourth of
July.''
   Golden Globes (comedy): Morgan Freeman, ``Driving Miss Daisy.''
   National Board of Review: Freeman.
   New York Film Critics Circle: Day-Lewis.
   National Society of Film Critics: Day-Lewis.
   Los Angeles Film Critics Association: Day-Lewis.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   BEST ACTRESS
   British Academy Awards: Pauline Collins, ``Shirley Valentine.''
   Golden Globes (drama): Michelle Pfeiffer, ``The Fabulous Baker
Boys.''
   Golden Globes (comedy): Jessica Tandy, ``Driving Miss Daisy.''
   National Board of Review: Ms. Pfeiffer.
   New York Film Critics Circle: Ms. Pfeiffer.
   National Society of Film Critics: Ms. Pfeiffer.
   Los Angeles Film Critics Association (tie): Andie MacDowell,
``sex, lies and videotape'' and Ms. Pfeiffer.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   BEST DIRECTOR
   Directors Guild of America: Oliver Stone, ``Born on the Fourth
of July.''
   British Academy Awards: Kenneth Branagh, ``Henry V.''
   Golden Globes: Stone.
   National Board of Review: Branagh.
   New York Film Critics Circle: Paul Mazursky, ``Enemies, A Love
Story.''
   National Society of Film Critics: Gus Van Sant, ``Drugstore
Cowboy.''
   Los Angeles Film Critics Association: Spike Lee, ``Do the Right
Thing.''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   BEST ORIGINAL SCREENPLAY
   Writers Guild of America: Woody Allen, ``Crimes and
Misdemeanors.''
   British Academy Awards: Nora Ephron, ``When Harry Met Sally...''
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   BEST ADAPTED SCREENPLAY
   Writers Guild of America: Alfred Uhry, ``Driving Miss Daisy.''
   Golden Globes: Oliver Stone and Ron Kovic, ``Born on the Fourth
of July.''
   New York Film Critics Circle: Gus Van Sant and Daniel Yost,
``Drugstore Cowboy.''
   National Society of Film Critics: Van Sant and Yost.
   Los Angeles Film Critics Association: Van Sant and Yost.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
